  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rajasthan Emergency Covid-19 Response Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Freedom Fund has established a Covid-19 Emergency Response Fund (ERF) to offer immediate humanitarian assistance through small-scale funding to some 100 frontline partners working with vulnerable communities in India, Nepal, Myanmar, Ethiopia, Thailand and Brazil (part of its established hotspot
programme).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project specifically provides:
1. Emergency relief to affected groups, including food, shelter, sanitation needs, protective equipment for shelter staff, transportation, healthcare-related costs. 
2. Surge capacity for NGO advocacy, to monitor needs of  vulnerable groups, ensure government response is appropriate and reaching those who need assistance. 
3. Microgrants to savings &amp; loans groups, self-help groups, and other existing community structures to provide credit and help absorb financial shocks.</narrative>
  </description>
